race.comment: FORAGOODCAUSE (4) brings a string of narrow defeats and comes back in grade off the latest at Warrnambool. Maps well and Yendall stays aboard. Finds the right race and deserves another chance. BALLYNACALLY (3) missed her hat-trick by a nose before the spell and has won two jumpouts in preparation for her return. Meech continues her association with the mare and she's a live chance. GRANDE TERRE (5) was a big Maiden winner, and he looked a run short resuming at Geelong. Has the early speed to clear the wide barrier and expect him to give a big sight. FOX MAN (8) was quickly back to his best winning a 65 at Mt Gambier. This is a bit tougher but he can't be ruled out. FINAL ATOM (2) has more to give and will get every chance from an inside barrier.
